## Directory Structure

```text
website/
│
├── index.html
└── style.css
```

---

## Upload to EC2

After creating both files:

```bash
sudo cp index.html /var/www/html/
sudo cp style.css /var/www/html/
```

Restart Apache:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart apache2
```

Open:

```text
http://<EC2-Public-IP>
```

---

## Upload to S3

1. Create S3 Bucket.
2. Upload:

   * index.html
   * style.css
3. Enable Static Website Hosting.
4. Make bucket public using Bucket Policy.
5. Open the S3 Website Endpoint URL.

This website is simple, attractive, and suitable for a Cloud Computing lab demonstration.
